work.work-title: Brightest and Best of the Stars of the Morning

credit.credit-words: Say, shall we yield Him, in costly devotion, Odors of Edom and offerings divine? Gems of the mountain and pearls of the ocean, Myrrh from the forest, or gold from the mine?
Brightest and Best of the Stars of the Morning
Brightest and best of the sons of the morning, Dawn on our darkness and lend us Thine aid; Star of the East, the horizon adorning, Guide where our infant Redeemer is laid.

direction-type.words: of the sons of the morning,
Vainly we offer each ample oblation,
Vainly with gifts would His favor
Richer by far is the heart's adoration,
Dearer to God are the prayers
